node.title: Woman with COVID-19 isolating in Hobart after arriving on Sydney flight
node.alt: The windows of rooms at the Fountainside accomodation with one room with closed curtains.
node.description: People who were on a Jetstar flight from Sydney to Hobart on Monday are asked to isolate after aÂ passenger tests positive for COVID-19.
node.content:
["Public health authorities are asking people who were on a flight from Sydney to Hobart on Monday to isolate immediately in the wake of a passenger testing\u00a0positive to COVID-19.\u00a0", "The affected flight is\u00a0Jetstar flight JQ-271 from Sydney to Hobart, which arrived at 11:42am.", "A Tasmanian woman aged in her 40s\u00a0who was on the flight tested positive to the virus yesterday.", "Health authorities said the woman had travelled from the United States via Sydney and had been in home quarantine since arriving in the state.", "She will be been taken to Hobart's medi-hotel Fountainside", "Passengers are being asked to isolate immediately and to contact the Public Health Hotline.", "Hobart Airport has been listed as a low-risk exposure site between 11:50am and 12:15pm on Monday.", "Anyone who was at the airport should get tested if they develop symptoms.\u00a0", "This\u00a0is the third recorded cases of COVID-19 in Tasmania over the past month.", "The others were an 18-month-old baby who arrived from Melbourne on November 18\u00a0and a man who intended to travel via Hobart to Melbourne from Brisbane.", "Premier Peter Gutwein said\u00a0Tasmania remained\u00a0on track to reopen its borders on December 15, despite parts of Sydney and the NSW Central Coast being placed on alert for the Omicron strain of COVID-19.", "Another returned traveller tested positive on Tuesday, the fifth confirmed case of the new variant of concern in New South Wales.", "In a statement, Mr Gutwein said there would\u00a0be strong protocols in place, including quarantine and testing for those who were\u00a0unvaccinated, and mandatory testing 72 hours prior to travel for people arriving from high-risk jurisdictions.", "", "
Heavily mutated Omicron variant puts scientist on alert
